{"type":"data","nodes":[{"type":"data","data":[{"debug":1},true],"uses":{}},{"type":"data","data":[{"zotero":1,"inscriptions":7},{"title":2,"author":3,"date":4,"citation":5,"uri":6},"Tavole greche de'magistrati annuali, scoperte ultimamente fra le rovine dell'antichissima città di Acre in Sicilia","Amati","1827","\u003Cspan>Girolamo Amati, «Tavole greche de’magistrati annuali, scoperte ultimamente fra le rovine dell’antichissima città di Acre in Sicilia», \u003Ci>Giornale Arcadico di scienze, lettere, ed arti\u003C/i> 35 (1827): 339–57, \u003Ca href=\"https://ia800903.us.archive.org/12/items/giornalearcadico35roma/giornalearcadico35roma.pdf\">https://ia800903.us.archive.org/12/items/giornalearcadico35roma/giornalearcadico35roma.pdf\u003C/a>\u003C/span>","https://www.zotero.org/groups/isicily/items/7CXM4Y52",[8],{"file":9,"uri":9,"title":10,"status":11,"editionAuthor":13,"type":14,"objectType":18,"material":22,"condition":26,"layoutDesc":28,"handNote":37,"date":55,"places":60,"geo":70,"provenance":62,"provenanceGeo":74,"country":75,"region":76,"settlement":66,"repository":77,"idno":81,"textLang":84,"tmNumber":88,"facsimile":89,"letterHeights":96,"publications":97,"zotero":103,"keywords":109,"html":119,"bibl":120},"ISic001031","Dedication recording board of magistrates",{"_":12},"draft",null,{"_":15,"ana":16,"ref":17},"dedication; list of magistrates","#function.dedication #function.list.magistrates","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/88.html",{"_":19,"ana":20,"ref":21},"base","#object.base","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/57.htm",{"_":23,"ana":24,"ref":25},"limestone","#material.stone.limestone","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/66.html",{"ana":27},"#condition.damaged",{"layout":29},{"p":30,"rs":31,"damage":35},"Line 1 is inscribed across the upper moulding (which is heavily damaged); the remainder of the text is engraved on the recessed front face, in two columns. The spacing between the columns after the first line is very irregular; column 2 has a half-line gap after line 2, meaning that the lines in the two columns are vertically out of synch after this point.",{"_":32,"ana":33,"ref":34},"chiselled","#execution.chiselled","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1",{"ana":36},"#text_condition.partly_illegible",{"lettering":38,"dimensions":39},"Neatly carved and regular letters, mostly without serifs, but some terminal wedges. Alpha with straight bar; epsilon on occasion has a slightly shorter mid-bar; zeta in form of I with wide horizontals; theta has short detached cross-bar; kappa has full-length arms; mu has vertical first and last, full length mid-strokes; xsi has three equal horiztonal bars; omicron is only slightly smaller than the other letters; pi has extended horizontal; rho has small rounded closed eye; sigma has horizontal top and bottom, with slihgtly variable mid-strokes; phi has small oval eye, with vertical often extended; omega is notably variable, always closed, but ranging from tear-drop to full circle on or even above and detached from the base line.",[40,46,51],{"type":41,"l":42,"from":43,"to":43,"h":44,"unit":45},"letterHeight","Line 1","line1","18","mm",{"type":41,"l":47,"from":48,"to":49,"h":50,"unit":45},"Line 2-23","line2","line23","11-15 (with omicron down to 9 and phi up to 20)",{"type":52,"l":53,"from":54,"to":48,"unit":45},"interlinear","Interlineation line 1 to 2","line",{"_":56,"notBefore":57,"notAfter":58,"evidence":59},"Later third or second century BCE on palaeographic grounds.",-250,-101,"lettering",[61,65],{"_":62,"type":63,"ref":64},"Acrae","ancient","http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462068",{"_":66,"type":67,"ref":68,"offset":69},"Palazzolo Acreide","modern","http://sws.geonames.org/2523922","near",[71],[72,73],37.0578,14.89346,[],"Italy","Sicily",{"_":78,"role":79,"ref":80},"Museo Archeologico Gabriele Judica","museum","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/102",{"_":82,"type":83},"2238","inventory",{"_":85,"mainLang":86,"languages":87},"Ancient Gr